---
When logging in this codebase (WatchAgent — app/services/, app/api/, app/repositories/):

LOGGER SETUP
- Always use structlog.get_logger(__name__) at module level. Never use print() or
  stdlib logging.info/warning/error directly in application code.
- stdlib logging.basicConfig() in poller_main.py is intentional — it wires
  third-party libraries into the structured pipeline. Do not remove it.

CONTEXT BINDING — bind before logging, not at the log call:
  - In app/services/poller.py:        bind(component="poller")
  - In app/services/weather_client.py: bind(city=city, component="weather_client")
  - In app/api/main.py middleware:     each request cleared via clear_contextvars();
                                       request_id, method, path set via bind_contextvars()
  - In app/repositories/:              no binding needed (caller provides context)

LOG LEVELS — use these exact event keys and fields:

  DEBUG:
    raw Open-Meteo API response body
      event key: "api_response_raw"
      fields:    body=response.text

  INFO:
    reading inserted (new or duplicate)
      event key: "reading_stored"
      fields:    city, timestamp, duplicate=True|False
    reading skipped as duplicate (emitted by ReadingRepository)
      event key: "reading_skipped"
      fields:    city, timestamp
    event passed cooldown and fired (emitted by EventDetector)
      event key: "weather_event_fired"
      fields:    city, event_type, <key_metric>=<value>, summary
                 where <key_metric> is the single most informative numeric field
                 (e.g. z_score for city_anomaly, delta for sudden_temp_drop, gap
                 for feels_like_gap, wind_speed for dangerous_wind, spread for
                 cross_city_divergence)
    event persisted to DB (emitted by EventRepository.insert)
      event key: "event_fired"
      fields:    city, event_type, timestamp, summary
    poll cycle summary (emitted by Poller after each complete cycle)
      event key: "poll_cycle_complete"
      fields:    cities_polled, new_readings, duplicates, events_fired, cycle_duration_ms
    API request completed (emitted by middleware in app/api/main.py)
      event key: "api_request"
      fields:    method, path, city_filter (str|null), results_returned (int|null),
                 duration_ms, status_code, request_id
    DB tables created
      event key: "db_init_complete"
    DB readiness confirmed
      event key: "db_ready"
      fields:    attempt

  WARNING:
    Open-Meteo poll failed after all retries
      event key: "poll_failed"
      fields:    city (str), http_status (int|None), attempt_count (int), error_msg (str)
      This is the ONLY warning type in the hot path.
    DB not ready, retrying
      event key: "db_not_ready_retrying"
      fields:    attempt, max_attempts, wait_seconds, error

  ERROR:
    Unexpected exception in reading handling, event persistence, or DB init
      event keys: "reading_handle_failed", "event_detection_failed",
                  "event_persist_failed", "db_init_failed", "reading_cycle_failed"
      ALL ERROR logs must include exc_info=True.

RULES:
- Duplicate readings (IntegrityError) are INFO with duplicate=True, never WARNING or ERROR.
- poll_failed must always carry all four fields: city, http_status, attempt_count, error_msg.
  http_status is None when the failure is not an HTTP status error (timeout, DNS, etc.).
- Every ERROR log must include exc_info=True so the stack trace is captured.
- Never log sensitive data (database credentials, API keys) at any level.
  Use mask_db_url() (app/config.py) for any log line that includes a DB URL.
